.TH TOUCH(1),User Commands,TOUCH(1)

.SH NAME
touch - create empty files

.SH SYNOPSIS
touch [-c] file ...

.SH DESCRIPTION
touch ensures that each named file exists.
For every operand, touch first tries to open the file for reading;
if that fails, it creates an empty file of the same name.

At least one file operand is required.

touch does not update access or modification times on files that already exist.

.SH OPTIONS
-c: Do not create missing files.
Files that already exist are still opened and closed;
files that do not exist are silently skipped.

.SH DIAGNOSTICS
touch: FILE: ... - a file could not be created.

.SH EXIT STATUS
0: All named files exist or were created.

1: No operand was given, an invalid option was supplied, or a file could not be created.
